1
00:00:55,342 --> 00:00:56,762
When people finish their day

2
00:00:57,177 --> 00:00:59,763
and hurry home,

3
00:01:00,556 --> 00:01:01,886
my day starts.

4
00:01:19,741 --> 00:01:22,411
My diner is open from midnight

5
00:01:22,995 --> 00:01:24,335
to seven in the morning.

6
00:01:25,414 --> 00:01:28,254
They call it "Midnight Diner."

7
00:01:33,172 --> 00:01:34,592
Do I even have customers?

8
00:01:35,132 --> 00:01:36,922
More than you would expect.

9
00:01:40,006 --> 00:01:42,827
MIDNIGHT DINER:
TOKYO STORIES

10
00:01:42,828 --> 00:01:47,959
HAM CUTLET

11
00:01:50,063 --> 00:01:51,193
Let's eat.

12
00:01:58,614 --> 00:02:01,124
It was Mr. Nakatsuka's first time
at my diner.

13
00:02:02,059 --> 00:02:06,359
He ate ham cutlets so fondly
that he made a strong impression.

14
00:02:08,874 --> 00:02:10,504
You make my mouth water.

15
00:02:12,127 --> 00:02:14,997
This is how ham cutlets
are supposed to be.

16
00:02:15,589 --> 00:02:18,339
The ham should be thin,
but the batter should be thick.

17
00:02:18,884 --> 00:02:21,554
These days many restaurants use
a thick slice of ham.

18
00:02:21,668 --> 00:02:22,708
Am I right?

19
00:02:23,138 --> 00:02:27,428
I've ordered it at a Western restaurant,
but I was so shocked.

20
00:02:28,143 --> 00:02:29,733
Their ham was so thick.

21
00:02:29,850 --> 00:02:31,980
And it was very high quality.

22
00:02:37,736 --> 00:02:39,606
Played with your little brother, huh?

23
00:02:40,489 --> 00:02:42,909
If you lost at Othello,

24
00:02:42,991 --> 00:02:45,241
you had to go out
and buy two ham cutlets.

25
00:02:46,635 --> 00:02:47,556
Have some more.

26
00:02:47,722 --> 00:02:51,667
I don't have any brothers,
so I envy you.

27
00:02:53,168 --> 00:02:55,248
Well, he's not a real brother.

28
00:02:55,837 --> 00:02:56,667
What?

29
00:02:57,839 --> 00:03:01,429
My brother is the son
of my father's second wife.

30
00:03:02,659 --> 00:03:06,659
We were only brothers for four years
until they got divorced.

31
00:03:07,891 --> 00:03:09,601
I was still in elementary school.

32
00:03:10,102 --> 00:03:12,102
It was several decades ago.

33
00:03:13,295 --> 00:03:15,505
Were you close, despite that?

34
00:03:17,234 --> 00:03:20,034
He was hot-tempered
but very friendly at the same time.

35
00:03:21,029 --> 00:03:22,569
He was so sweet.

36
00:03:23,865 --> 00:03:25,785
It was so tough

37
00:03:26,201 --> 00:03:27,371
when we were separated.

38
00:03:27,869 --> 00:03:30,749
It's a good story.
Don't you think, Master?

39
00:03:32,124 --> 00:03:34,424
And where is your brother now?

40
00:03:35,043 --> 00:03:38,303
After our parents were divorced,
I lost track of him.

41
00:03:39,326 --> 00:03:42,286
Unfortunately,
I haven't seen him for decades.

42
00:03:48,268 --> 00:03:50,138
- Hello.
- Welcome.

43
00:03:50,726 --> 00:03:51,926
Beer for starters.

44
00:03:52,573 --> 00:03:53,403
Sure.

45
00:03:55,856 --> 00:03:56,806
Hey, Master.

46
00:03:57,399 --> 00:03:58,519
I think you can tell

47
00:03:58,638 --> 00:04:01,308
someone's true character
if you see how he departs.

48
00:04:02,446 --> 00:04:03,276
Here you go.

49
00:04:05,037 --> 00:04:06,077
What happened?

50
00:04:06,742 --> 00:04:08,597
My friend is getting a divorce.

51
00:04:08,597 --> 00:04:11,887
They're having an ugly fight
over their pet rabbit.

52
00:04:12,575 --> 00:04:15,093
- Dumping it onto each other?
- No, the opposite.

53
00:04:15,432 --> 00:04:16,722
Both want to keep it.

54
00:04:17,833 --> 00:04:20,172
- Sounds like a kid.
- I know.

55
00:04:20,172 --> 00:04:21,962
They're holding their ground.

56
00:04:23,086 --> 00:04:25,966
According to law,
a pet is considered property.

57
00:04:26,386 --> 00:04:30,349
Whoever keeps the pet has
to relinquish other property

58
00:04:30,349 --> 00:04:32,331
or give money to the other person.

59
00:04:32,332 --> 00:04:34,412
That's how most cases are settled.

60
00:04:34,639 --> 00:04:37,133
Really? I didn't know that.

61
00:04:38,673 --> 00:04:40,723
Sorry to jump in your conversation.

62
00:04:41,865 --> 00:04:42,695
I'm...

63
00:04:43,351 --> 00:04:44,681
Nakatsuka.

64
00:04:45,156 --> 00:04:47,430
ATTORNEY
YUKIO NAKATSUKA

65
00:04:47,431 --> 00:04:49,541
Huh? You're an attorney?

66
00:04:54,390 --> 00:04:56,060
Your office is in this area?

67
00:04:56,728 --> 00:04:58,558
Has it been there for a long time?

68
00:04:58,713 --> 00:05:00,877
Yes. For 35 years.

69
00:05:01,129 --> 00:05:02,839
Thirty-five years? Wow?

70
00:05:03,460 --> 00:05:06,960
But I'll be closing the office next month.

71
00:05:07,826 --> 00:05:08,846
May I ask why?

72
00:05:10,301 --> 00:05:12,891
Because times have changed.

73
00:05:14,288 --> 00:05:17,038
"Old soldiers just fade away."

74
00:05:26,113 --> 00:05:29,920
In a municipally-owned apartment
that will be torn down next January,

75
00:05:29,920 --> 00:05:32,785
government officials tried to convince

76
00:05:32,786 --> 00:05:36,549
a resident who refuses to leave
to come to the negotiating table.

77
00:05:43,255 --> 00:05:45,338
Mr. Ishibashi! Please, Mr. Ishibashi!

78
00:05:45,338 --> 00:05:46,593
Please!

79
00:05:46,925 --> 00:05:47,935
Go away!

80
00:05:49,511 --> 00:05:51,760
Calm down, Mr. Ishibashi, please!

81
00:05:53,890 --> 00:05:55,020
This is my home.

82
00:05:55,558 --> 00:06:00,728
My late mother and I
worked so hard to keep it!

83
00:06:01,218 --> 00:06:05,496
Nobody can take it away from me!

84
00:06:05,994 --> 00:06:09,244
Government officials said
that demolition work will start soon...

85
00:06:10,996 --> 00:06:13,581
I've sorted out all the
financial documents.

86
00:06:13,581 --> 00:06:16,793
Take a look at the rest to decide
which ones you keep at home

87
00:06:17,247 --> 00:06:19,117
and which ones you dispose of.

88
00:06:21,251 --> 00:06:22,171
Sure.

89
00:06:23,461 --> 00:06:26,631
Administrative subrogation could be
an option...

90
00:06:29,782 --> 00:06:30,952
Go away!

91
00:06:31,511 --> 00:06:33,971
- Thank you for the meal.
- Thank you for coming.

92
00:06:38,435 --> 00:06:40,315
I saw that on the evening news.

93
00:06:41,354 --> 00:06:44,484
The government will appeal
to administrative subrogation.

94
00:06:44,613 --> 00:06:46,059
It's just a matter of time.

95
00:06:46,265 --> 00:06:47,225
I guess so.

96
00:06:47,642 --> 00:06:49,102
What are you talking about?

97
00:06:49,446 --> 00:06:52,026
To build the Olympic stadium,

98
00:06:52,185 --> 00:06:55,195
they have to demolish
an old municipally-owned apartment.

99
00:06:55,531 --> 00:06:58,291
An old man refuses to leave
and is causing trouble.

100
00:06:58,725 --> 00:07:00,105
Chu, you hadn't heard?

101
00:07:00,415 --> 00:07:04,085
The old man is obnoxious and curses
down at the government officials.

102
00:07:04,200 --> 00:07:07,200
No electricity, no gas.
Yet he stays there by himself.

103
00:07:07,450 --> 00:07:10,040
But it's a municipally-owned apartment,
right?

104
00:07:10,187 --> 00:07:11,687
He doesn't own the property.

105
00:07:11,998 --> 00:07:14,708
He has to leave sooner or later.

106
00:07:15,226 --> 00:07:17,186
It must be a special place to him.

107
00:07:17,682 --> 00:07:19,732
Don't you feel any sympathy?

108
00:07:21,102 --> 00:07:22,392
- I do, but...
- Here.

109
00:07:22,463 --> 00:07:24,343
- Enjoy your ham cutlets.
- Thank you.

110
00:07:25,971 --> 00:07:28,391
Ham cutlet, huh?
It's a good old-fashioned dish.

111
00:07:29,347 --> 00:07:33,347
I often ate it at a local butcher's shop
when I was a kid.

112
00:07:34,595 --> 00:07:38,265
The community was tighter.
Oh, the good old days.

113
00:07:38,538 --> 00:07:41,578
Come on, Chu. Don't be so nostalgic.

114
00:07:42,754 --> 00:07:44,624
You're too young to understand.

115
00:07:46,059 --> 00:07:47,399
If you glorify the past,

116
00:07:47,524 --> 00:07:51,944
you won't be happy with the present
and the future, which are more important.

117
00:07:53,308 --> 00:07:54,768
You're right.

118
00:07:55,592 --> 00:07:57,342
The young lady is absolutely right.

119
00:07:59,614 --> 00:08:00,664
Young lady?

120
00:08:48,919 --> 00:08:50,184
People finish their day

121
00:08:50,428 --> 00:08:52,428
and hurry home.

122
00:08:54,258 --> 00:08:57,468
But sometimes they don't want
to go straight back home,

123
00:08:58,241 --> 00:09:00,491
so they drop in somewhere
on the way home.

124
00:09:02,241 --> 00:09:03,451
Have some.

125
00:09:03,697 --> 00:09:05,197
Thank you.

126
00:09:05,579 --> 00:09:07,539
I don't mean it.

127
00:09:07,653 --> 00:09:09,323
You gave me a whole melon,

128
00:09:09,664 --> 00:09:11,494
but I can't finish it by myself.

129
00:09:25,731 --> 00:09:27,991
I've run a small law office by myself.

130
00:09:28,810 --> 00:09:31,060
I believe that I worked hard,

131
00:09:32,238 --> 00:09:35,568
but the number of my clients
has declined drastically.

132
00:09:36,263 --> 00:09:38,933
You've worked for 35 years.

133
00:09:39,866 --> 00:09:41,236
It's an accomplishment.

134
00:09:41,581 --> 00:09:44,341
I started the firm with my wife.

135
00:09:45,330 --> 00:09:46,830
Two years ago,

136
00:09:47,344 --> 00:09:48,884
I lost her.

137
00:09:50,039 --> 00:09:54,459
I think I may have lost my passion
after that.

138
00:09:56,812 --> 00:09:58,232
Would you like ham cutlet?

139
00:09:59,471 --> 00:10:00,301
Wait.

140
00:10:00,667 --> 00:10:02,037
Not tonight.

141
00:10:02,932 --> 00:10:03,762
I see.

142
00:10:04,327 --> 00:10:05,377
An unusual day, huh?

143
00:10:07,956 --> 00:10:10,416
I've found my little brother.

144
00:10:11,929 --> 00:10:12,849
Really?

145
00:10:13,404 --> 00:10:14,694
I'm happy for you.

146
00:10:15,021 --> 00:10:17,441
He actually lives nearby.

147
00:10:17,621 --> 00:10:20,783
- Really? Then...
- No.

148
00:10:21,668 --> 00:10:23,798
I've wanted to see him so badly,

149
00:10:24,708 --> 00:10:27,298
but I got intimidated
when the moment arrived.

150
00:10:28,558 --> 00:10:29,648
Why?

151
00:10:30,943 --> 00:10:31,783
The other day,

152
00:10:32,363 --> 00:10:34,413
I talked about the game Othello, right?

153
00:10:34,808 --> 00:10:35,648
Yeah.

154
00:10:36,067 --> 00:10:39,157
You played against your brother
for ham cutlets.

155
00:10:40,762 --> 00:10:42,632
I always won

156
00:10:43,116 --> 00:10:46,876
and made my brother pay
for ham cutlets.

157
00:10:48,004 --> 00:10:50,844
He ran out of his allowance

158
00:10:51,641 --> 00:10:53,101
and extorted money

159
00:10:54,093 --> 00:10:55,803
from his classmate.

160
00:10:57,850 --> 00:10:59,890
When the school found out,

161
00:11:00,553 --> 00:11:01,973
he was questioned.

162
00:11:03,308 --> 00:11:06,768
But he didn't say anything
about our game.

163
00:11:08,519 --> 00:11:09,979
He protected me.

164
00:11:11,528 --> 00:11:12,398
I guess...

165
00:11:13,582 --> 00:11:17,632
he didn't want to upset
his newly-acquired big brother.

166
00:11:22,106 --> 00:11:23,766
My father hit him so hard

167
00:11:24,674 --> 00:11:27,254
as punishment.

168
00:11:29,032 --> 00:11:30,242
I felt so guilty.

169
00:11:30,712 --> 00:11:32,172
It was my fault.

170
00:11:34,167 --> 00:11:36,677
I watched silently as my brother...

171
00:11:37,753 --> 00:11:39,253
was beaten.

172
00:11:42,218 --> 00:11:45,058
I was scared of my father.

173
00:11:47,047 --> 00:11:49,007
I was afraid that he might abandon me.

174
00:11:49,987 --> 00:11:51,277
Just like my real mother.

175
00:11:55,121 --> 00:11:56,121
My little brother...

176
00:11:56,815 --> 00:11:58,815
smiled at me

177
00:11:59,377 --> 00:12:00,837
when my eyes met his,

178
00:12:01,543 --> 00:12:03,083
as he was being beaten.

179
00:12:04,372 --> 00:12:05,292
He was saying:

180
00:12:05,900 --> 00:12:07,280
"I'm okay."

181
00:12:11,588 --> 00:12:14,208
You can't shake the guilty feeling, huh?

182
00:12:15,398 --> 00:12:16,398
Well...

183
00:12:17,210 --> 00:12:18,790
my remorse is

184
00:12:19,520 --> 00:12:21,400
like a hangnail, nothing too serious.

185
00:12:26,662 --> 00:12:27,992
They say...

186
00:12:28,380 --> 00:12:29,970
that you might get tetanus

187
00:12:30,411 --> 00:12:32,661
if you don't treat the hangnail.

188
00:12:40,077 --> 00:12:40,907
Go away!

189
00:12:42,436 --> 00:12:43,800
Go away, asshole!

190
00:12:43,801 --> 00:12:45,134
Don't upset him.

191
00:12:45,134 --> 00:12:46,224
Go away!

192
00:12:48,513 --> 00:12:50,353
Let's discuss it over there.

193
00:13:02,005 --> 00:13:03,255
Who the hell are you?

194
00:13:05,417 --> 00:13:07,168
If you don't go, you'll get wet!

195
00:13:07,335 --> 00:13:08,175
Kenta.

196
00:13:13,574 --> 00:13:14,404
It's me.

197
00:13:17,709 --> 00:13:18,999
Long time, no see.

198
00:13:24,463 --> 00:13:25,303
Big brother?

199
00:13:34,731 --> 00:13:37,861
Really? You're a lawyer, huh?

200
00:13:38,317 --> 00:13:39,737
I'm proud of you.

201
00:13:40,309 --> 00:13:42,189
I failed the bar exam so many times,

202
00:13:42,489 --> 00:13:44,239
you shouldn't be proud.

203
00:13:44,563 --> 00:13:47,363
- Here you go.
- Just like the good old days.

204
00:13:48,411 --> 00:13:49,501
Let's eat.

205
00:14:00,126 --> 00:14:01,376
It's delicious.

206
00:14:08,037 --> 00:14:10,997
How long are you planning to stay there?

207
00:14:15,161 --> 00:14:16,451
Why do you ask?

208
00:14:17,856 --> 00:14:20,196
The electricity and gas
were already cut off.

209
00:14:20,341 --> 00:14:22,431
How can you survive?

210
00:14:24,713 --> 00:14:25,633
Leave me alone.

211
00:14:26,355 --> 00:14:27,695
This doesn't concern you.

212
00:14:28,552 --> 00:14:31,052
They will start the demolition soon.

213
00:14:31,950 --> 00:14:32,990
They will...

214
00:14:33,872 --> 00:14:35,912
remove you by force.

215
00:14:36,871 --> 00:14:38,711
Go ahead. I'm not worried.

216
00:14:40,239 --> 00:14:42,319
Even if I'm torn apart
by a power shovel,

217
00:14:42,415 --> 00:14:43,875
I won't leave that place.

218
00:14:45,385 --> 00:14:47,385
You're still so stubborn, huh?

219
00:14:51,907 --> 00:14:52,947
Is this...?

220
00:14:53,515 --> 00:14:55,395
It's the one we played with.

221
00:14:56,015 --> 00:14:56,975
I kept it.

222
00:14:58,406 --> 00:15:01,036
Master, you don't mind if I open it here?

223
00:15:03,363 --> 00:15:04,243
Not at all.

224
00:15:09,074 --> 00:15:11,784
What do you think? Want to play?

225
00:15:15,107 --> 00:15:16,057
Play for what?

226
00:15:17,286 --> 00:15:18,536
If you win,

227
00:15:18,804 --> 00:15:21,474
I will buy
as many ham cutlets as you want.

228
00:15:22,220 --> 00:15:23,130
And beer.

229
00:15:24,939 --> 00:15:26,269
If I win,

230
00:15:27,017 --> 00:15:28,817
you must leave the apartment.

231
00:15:35,013 --> 00:15:39,223
It is not the best place
for you to live anymore.

232
00:15:44,856 --> 00:15:46,146
Fine. Then I'll beat you.

233
00:15:46,733 --> 00:15:47,693
Brother,

234
00:15:48,546 --> 00:15:49,886
I'm better now.

235
00:15:51,523 --> 00:15:52,813
We shall see.

236
00:15:59,190 --> 00:16:02,780
When I grow up, I'll be rich
and build a huge house.

237
00:16:03,770 --> 00:16:04,770
And live with Mom.

238
00:16:05,235 --> 00:16:06,895
Brother, you can live with me.

239
00:16:07,252 --> 00:16:09,212
Dad can't, because he beats Mom.

240
00:16:25,443 --> 00:16:28,649
Good. I won. Go and buy the usual ones.

241
00:16:28,649 --> 00:16:31,922
Give me another chance.
If I lose again, then I'll buy.

242
00:16:31,923 --> 00:16:35,093
- Please.
- No. Crying won't erase your loss.

243
00:16:35,343 --> 00:16:37,933
Fine. I go and buy it, right?

244
00:16:38,289 --> 00:16:39,999
I'll win the next one anyway.

245
00:16:40,640 --> 00:16:42,940
This one... and this one.

246
00:16:44,916 --> 00:16:48,786
Is the house we used to live in
still there?

247
00:16:49,597 --> 00:16:50,967
No. It's gone.

248
00:16:51,837 --> 00:16:53,957
A tall building stands there now.

249
00:16:54,524 --> 00:16:55,774
I see.

250
00:16:57,201 --> 00:17:00,531
Why is that apartment
so important to you?

251
00:17:02,782 --> 00:17:04,952
I've lived there for most of my life.

252
00:17:06,066 --> 00:17:07,276
Mother died there.

253
00:17:07,647 --> 00:17:09,187
I'll die there, too.

254
00:17:10,988 --> 00:17:12,375
You haven't changed much.

255
00:17:12,375 --> 00:17:15,665
You have no strategy
for playing this game.

256
00:17:18,002 --> 00:17:20,382
I'm not interested in a tiny victory.

257
00:17:21,077 --> 00:17:23,657
I still have a chance
to come from behind to win.

258
00:17:31,921 --> 00:17:32,841
Oh, no...

259
00:17:33,673 --> 00:17:35,383
Here you go.

260
00:17:57,160 --> 00:17:58,250
Do I have to pass?

261
00:18:03,540 --> 00:18:04,380
Look.

262
00:18:13,921 --> 00:18:15,461
I lost.

263
00:18:18,381 --> 00:18:21,011
What's wrong with you, brother?

264
00:18:21,348 --> 00:18:22,968
Did you lose it to your old age?

265
00:18:24,465 --> 00:18:26,936
Master, beer, please.

266
00:18:26,937 --> 00:18:28,517
- Two bottles.
- Sure.

267
00:18:30,426 --> 00:18:32,716
Don't be bothered. I'll get them myself.

268
00:18:36,444 --> 00:18:37,364
Let me open it.

269
00:18:38,108 --> 00:18:39,948
Master, would you like some beer?

270
00:18:40,823 --> 00:18:42,163
- What do you say?
- But...

271
00:18:43,117 --> 00:18:44,987
- Go ahead.
- I'm really sorry.

272
00:18:46,479 --> 00:18:47,809
You can't do that.

273
00:18:48,039 --> 00:18:50,789
"Crying won't erase your loss."
You always said that.

274
00:18:51,487 --> 00:18:54,697
I just watched
while my father beat you up.

275
00:18:55,032 --> 00:18:56,122
I'm so sorry.

276
00:19:01,844 --> 00:19:04,604
It was a long time ago.
I forgot about it.

277
00:19:06,366 --> 00:19:08,351
I will negotiate with the government

278
00:19:08,351 --> 00:19:10,188
and get you the best compensation

279
00:19:10,189 --> 00:19:12,149
in return for vacating the apartment.

280
00:19:12,705 --> 00:19:14,045
I'm a lawyer.

281
00:19:14,398 --> 00:19:16,268
Let me do what I can.

282
00:19:16,848 --> 00:19:18,808
Come on. I won.

283
00:19:19,590 --> 00:19:20,943
That's not what we agreed on.

284
00:19:21,084 --> 00:19:23,134
I've already found a new place for you.

285
00:19:23,927 --> 00:19:25,982
It's smaller than your current place,

286
00:19:26,202 --> 00:19:28,622
but it's tidy and has good sunlight.

287
00:19:28,933 --> 00:19:30,103
And the rent is cheap.

288
00:19:30,790 --> 00:19:33,630
If you don't like it, I can find another.

289
00:19:34,997 --> 00:19:37,787
Or you can live with me...

290
00:19:38,798 --> 00:19:41,588
if you don't mind.

291
00:19:42,697 --> 00:19:44,287
I have an extra room anyway.

292
00:19:44,733 --> 00:19:46,863
Both of us are single.

293
00:19:47,924 --> 00:19:51,004
Would it be so bad to spend
a quiet retirement life together?

294
00:19:51,388 --> 00:19:53,518
We can play Othello once in a while.

295
00:19:54,218 --> 00:19:55,218
Idiot!

296
00:20:02,351 --> 00:20:04,481
Don't spoil me.

297
00:20:11,525 --> 00:20:12,865
Just think about it.

298
00:20:27,430 --> 00:20:29,640
- See you later.
- Thank you.

299
00:20:29,724 --> 00:20:31,564
- Bye.
- Hey, brother.

300
00:20:39,525 --> 00:20:40,535
After that,

301
00:20:41,027 --> 00:20:44,277
Mr. Nakatsuka negotiated
with the government

302
00:20:44,780 --> 00:20:47,820
and brought both sides to terms
on how to solve the issue.

303
00:20:48,034 --> 00:20:52,374
His brother finally agreed
to leave the apartment.

304
00:21:20,492 --> 00:21:21,412
That means...

305
00:21:22,526 --> 00:21:26,066
I was preparing to live with him
at my place.

306
00:21:26,364 --> 00:21:29,074
But he wanted to take
the biggest gamble of his life

307
00:21:29,613 --> 00:21:33,163
with the compensation money
for his forced removal.

308
00:21:37,848 --> 00:21:39,732
And he won big at a casino

309
00:21:39,919 --> 00:21:42,068
and bought a mansion
with a pool overseas.

310
00:21:42,269 --> 00:21:43,609
Unbelievable.

311
00:21:44,618 --> 00:21:45,618
He wants...

312
00:21:46,271 --> 00:21:49,941
me to go over there
and live with him.

313
00:21:50,676 --> 00:21:51,676
Are you going?

314
00:21:53,688 --> 00:21:55,278
- Hello.
- Welcome.

315
00:21:55,371 --> 00:21:58,201
Mr. Nakatsuka, regarding the case
from the other day...

316
00:21:59,010 --> 00:22:00,680
I have some information here.

317
00:22:01,262 --> 00:22:03,209
My friend has a personal debt issue

318
00:22:03,210 --> 00:22:05,380
and I want to ask Mr. Nakatsuka
for advice.

319
00:22:05,861 --> 00:22:10,321
Even though I closed the office,
I still have a license.

320
00:22:11,180 --> 00:22:13,550
I can still work.

321
00:22:17,829 --> 00:22:19,119
Let's see...

322
00:22:19,750 --> 00:22:20,920
This document is here.

323
00:22:21,418 --> 00:22:24,798
This is a table of contents.

324
00:22:24,934 --> 00:22:27,774
Both of you have a good look.

325
00:22:36,367 --> 00:22:38,179
When you make ham cutlets,

326
00:22:38,180 --> 00:22:41,421
most importantly, make sure
that the flour doesn't get lumpy.

327
00:22:41,943 --> 00:22:44,827
Coat it with bread crumbs evenly
and firmly.

328
00:22:44,984 --> 00:22:46,284
Here you go.

329
00:22:49,585 --> 00:22:51,415
What's the best strategy to win?

330
00:22:51,574 --> 00:22:52,534
I don't know.

331
00:23:41,031 --> 00:23:46,054
THIS STORY IS FICTION

